column7: A stationary exercise bike that includes a foot-exercise
mechanism that rotates and a hand-exercise mechanism
that rotates. ln addition to the rotational movement,
both the foot-exercise mechanism and the hand-exercise
mechanism simultaneously move in a reciprocating
manner. The foot-exercise mechanism makes recipro
cating upward and downward movements in a vertical
plane and the hand-exercise mechanism makes recipro
cation forward and backward movements in a horizon
tal plane. The height of the hand-exercise `mechanism
and the seat ofthe bike are adjustable, so that they may
be positioned at a proper height and angle.
